techmeme.title: Salesforce reports Q4 revenue up 8% YoY to $9.99B, vs. $10.04B est., and forecasts FY 2026 revenue below estimates; CRM drops 5%+ after hours (Zaheer Kachwala/Reuters)
Hume launches Octave, an LLM for text-to-speech that generates custom AI voices with adjustable emotions, offering a free tier with 10,000 characters per month (Carl Franzen/VentureBeat)
Google says it received FDA clearance for the Pixel Watch 3's Loss of Pulse Detection feature, available in the EU and rolling out in the US at the end of March (Abner Li/9to5Google)
Microsoft says it completed a multi-year project, the EU Data Boundary for the Microsoft Cloud, to let Europe-based cloud customers store and process data in EU (Kyle Wiggers/TechCrunch)
Google redesigns Results About You, its tool for requesting the removal of Search results with personal info, adding a new hub and the ability to update results (Jeremy Gan/Engadget)
